headline.main: Don’t Care for This Impeachment? Wait Until Next Year

docs.abstract: Victories by Jon Ossoff and the Rev. Raphael Warnock, which were overshadowed by violence from Trump supporters in Washington, will reshape the balance of power in Congress.
docs.snippet: Victories by Jon Ossoff and the Rev. Raphael Warnock, which were overshadowed by violence from Trump supporters in Washington, will reshape the balance of power in Congress.
docs.lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — Jon Ossoff completed a Democratic sweep of Georgia’s Senate runoffs on Wednesday, a striking political validation for his party in a state that has been challenging for Democrats for most of the last two decades.

headline.main: Democrats Win Both Georgia Races to Gain Control of Senate

byline.original: By Richard Fausset, Jonathan Martin and Stephanie Saul

docs.abstract: Teenage comments in response to our recent writing prompts, and an invitation to join the ongoing conversation.
docs.snippet: Teenage comments in response to our recent writing prompts, and an invitation to join the ongoing conversation.
docs.lead_paragraph: For this week’s roundup of student comments on our writing prompts, we asked teenagers to share with us the objects that are bringing them comfort in these uncertain times, tell us about the values they’ve learned from television, and analyze the messages in an illustration related to the upcoming election.

headline.main: What Students Are Saying About Objects of Comfort, Lessons From TV and Political Divisions

docs.abstract: The outspoken owner of the Cowboys says his players will not be allowed to stay in the locker room during the anthem, regardless of league policy.
docs.snippet: The outspoken owner of the Cowboys says his players will not be allowed to stay in the locker room during the anthem, regardless of league policy.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Dallas Cowboys owner Jerry Jones, no stranger to speaking his mind and creating controversy, on Wednesday added fuel to an already confusing and rancorous debate about how the N.F.L. plans to handle players who demonstrate during the playing of the national anthem this season.

headline.main: Defying N.F.L., Jerry Jones Says Players Must Stand for Anthem
headline.print_headline: Defying N.F.L., Cowboys’ Owner Says His Players Must Stand for the Anthem

docs.lead_paragraph: This article is part of our latest special report on Museums, which focuses on reopening, reinvention and resilience.

docs.abstract: The marketing business is going through a period of innovation as it sheds workers and tries to hold on to clients.
docs.snippet: The marketing business is going through a period of innovation as it sheds workers and tries to hold on to clients.
docs.lead_paragraph: The advertising industry’s tendency toward excess — catered parties in Las Vegas headlined by pop stars; unwieldy internal hierarchies stuffed with countless director roles; throw-it-at-the-wall ad placement — has persisted for years despite concerns about wastefulness.

headline.main: ‘A Big Correction’: Pandemic Brings Change to ‘Bloated’ Ad Industry
headline.print_headline: Party’s Over as Ad Industry Adapts in Pandemic

docs.abstract: A group of academics gathered to write a first scholarly history of the Trump administration. How do you contextualize a presidency that, as one put it, may have “jumped the shark”?
docs.snippet: A group of academics gathered to write a first scholarly history of the Trump administration. How do you contextualize a presidency that, as one put it, may have “jumped the shark”?
docs.lead_paragraph: From the day he took office, Donald J. Trump had America’s historians on high alert, as they took to news programs, Op-Ed pages and social media to help contextualize every norm-busting twist and turn (and tweet).

headline.main: The Trump Presidency Is History. They’re Writing the First Draft.
headline.print_headline: Trump Joins The Pages Of History

docs.abstract: The former officer, Robert Olsen, was acquitted of murder charges, but was found guilty on lesser counts after the fatal shooting of Anthony Hill, an unarmed Air Force veteran.
docs.snippet: The former officer, Robert Olsen, was acquitted of murder charges, but was found guilty on lesser counts after the fatal shooting of Anthony Hill, an unarmed Air Force veteran.
docs.lead_paragraph: DECATUR, Ga. — A former Georgia police officer was convicted on Monday in connection with the shooting death of an unarmed black man whom the officer had found wandering naked outside an apartment complex in 2015.

headline.main: Former Georgia Officer Who Killed a Black Man Is Convicted, but Not of Murder
headline.print_headline: Jury Acquits Former Officer Of Murder

docs.abstract: Culture wars, fueled by Fox News-style provocation, have arrived in France.
docs.snippet: Culture wars, fueled by Fox News-style provocation, have arrived in France.
docs.lead_paragraph: PARIS — It’s become a familiar refrain in French political life. From President Emmanuel Macron and his cabinet to the far-right opposition, from print columnists to talking heads, “Americanization” is increasingly held responsible for a whole set of social ills ailing the nation.

headline.main: France Is Becoming More Like America. It’s Terrible.
